      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GAELIC GEM (8) lightly raced filly with her hoof on the till. On the quick back up after sitting on the fast pace with a game third over 1300m at Canberra in a decent rating contest. Well drawn again and should prove too good for these. OL' MATE COOP (3) first run for the Beer & Carpenter yard he failed to keep up over the unsuitable 1000m when sixth at Kembla Grange. Tongue-tie goes on and is proven at this trip. Will find this more to his liking. NORTH STAR MISS (10) resumes for her second campaign. Outclassed on debut when fifth to the progressive Master Of The Air over 1200m at Kembla Grange last September. Wasn't pushed out when sixth in a recent 800m trial at Kembla Grange. Keep safe. LEON RUBEN (2) looks the pick of the rest as he returns for his second prep.",
